content: Wish to see more games like this!
I like it c:
This game has given me joy since the year it released. One of the best games on any/all mobiles handsdown.
One of few good mobile games

So much fun, sci fi problem solving. Quite challenging but not too much to stop me keeping trying (in easy mode!!) Creative ideas and nicely done simple graphics. It would be good to have something to rewind to a last saved pont or something.
Please do a super easy mode. It is a cell phone game not a computer game

It's a very challenging game, the difficulty of the game makes me uninstall it sometimes, but I love everything else, the art, the music, the mechanics.... It just needs an "relaxing difficulty". My daily life is already stressing on its on, I just wanna explore the space to relax a bit.
Very cool game, like the overall atmosphere, the context and so on... but it's maybe too difficult. Had to read some stuff online to get to endings other than 1 which is quite easily attainable.
Masterpiece
Classic

I found this endlessly dull and very repetitive. Survive as long as you can through what basically amounts to rolling the dice. Little to no gameplay or skill involved. Just luck and maybe a smidge of common sense. It's pretty enough and good for a few run throughs.

The cocoons in omega edition does not work when it grows into a ship. I can't visit any other stars even though I have a space folder. I wish you had a log feature for solar systems which you have visited. You can then go back to a space ship you have found if your current one is in bad shape.
I love this game, but whenever I quit, it doesn't properly save so when I come back to it I'm way farther back than I used to be before
Wondrous

A failure simulator that you get to pay for! Even on "easy" I had 50 deaths before the first milestone - and the game loop is so repetitive I wanted to uninstall this almost as soon as I downloaded it. This is a phone game, I don't want to have to read a walkthrough just to attain some persistent progress. Total waste of time.
This game is interesting, but not fun. It's got all the guaranteed loss of gambling... and that's it.
Booooring

An atmospheric but dreadfully tedious game. The game is a good idea with superb atmosphere but there's just no incentive to play the game. No battle. No tactics. It's just random resource management with very little actual management. You're better off just playing lottery.
Involving, fun, clever, thematic... Outstanding.

Great game overall but gave 4 stars in the end because achievements don't 
work and I can't sync with my Google play account, which is frustrating 
seeing as it's a paid app. This means that despite beating the game several 
times the progress and achievements may not transfer if I switch devices 
Seems as though some other people have the same problem so it would be 
great if the problem could be fixed.
Well made. But after a dozen plays I don't see the game. It's punishing and tedious.
Time heals all wounds and this game just feels right now. Wonderful little rogue-em'-up with a sense of timeless adventure.

I used to enjoy this game. But after the Omega update, it feels like punishment. It's like dark souls in space, except based on a random number generator instead of skill having any role in it. I rarely make it more than 5-10 systems in before random events, and zero garden planets, leave me with no hull or no air. Seriously don't buy this. I wish i could just roll this back to the previous edition.
Great game. Playing a lot. Returning often :)
Swiat zalewa fala darmowego syfu,a gry takie jak Battlevoid Harbinger,Out There,Rusted Warfare nikt nie zna. Jak to mozliwe?
Buggy. My new technologies keep being replaced with copies of older ones on the list. Some store spaces on ships aren't accessible by touchscreen...
Games are too short

Really fun game. Definitely some ftl vibes with the storied "combat". But, has its own unique resource management systems. Can get pretty repetitive after winning a few times in different ways. Also a quick mention the previous app icon was imo a LOT better. This one looks too generic, my eyes glide right over it. But that's a small small gripe. Really happy with my purchase.

After a lot of playing, it could use some tuning on the difficulty. Unless you are super lucky it basically impossible to get anywhere. Very well made game in all other respects! No microtransaction bs.
Hard but really fun

I love roguelikes, etc, so I expect frequent deaths, but even with that, it seems like you need a frustratingly specific run to succeed. I'm open to the idea that I need to be better at the game, but while this is a technically sound game, totally worth trying, my losses felt unfair, in a way I learned nothing from, instead of "oh ok, if I do x better, it won't happen again." 100% try, 40% keep.

I respect its artistic imagery and chilling poetics. However, I find the strategy shallow and winning overly hard, even on "Easy". Resource acquisition and management feels tedious, visiting planet after planet and executing the same actions in the same order--orbit, land, drill, add resources, take-off, travel, repeat. I've completed two of the missions failed for many hours on the others and have grown weary of striking out there in the void.
Great game, great devs, I also own the game on steam. I support the devs because I should if I wanna see more good games in the future.

I bought this game long time and subscribe that the developer still update new content. Try this game and you will realise it worth every buck. P/s. There are a bug that when i die because out of shield point, the game not end and i jump to another ship. This happen when i try to collect fuel from a star.
That gfx is not really my cup of tea.

This game is at once beautifully thematic, crazy addictive, band as brutally difficult as you can imagine. Yet, you'll find yourself wanting to keep coming back because it is indeed that interesting and fun. Worth it.
Hit a dead end where you're space folder range unable to reach other star system.
Deceptively simple, it's tricky and mysterious, love it.

needs balancing, not enough cargo spaces on most ships, the 3space ship is useless, too much rng on the planet encounters and materials, too grindy to complete and hard to finish even on easy. Glitchy on exploring map without telescope. Glitchy on selecting random ship existing room slot (ie to dismantle). 90% of the text encounters are destructive. Narrow tech path to reach to an ending, during the last space exploration, planets are far from one another. Annoying rng gameplay.

This is my current obsession, a surprisingly gripping sci fi adventure considering the simplicity of the design. The visuals are excellent and gameplay manages to be nail biting without leaning on combat or animation
I could dump a lot of time into this game.
does not work anymore, splash screen and nothing

I bet it's great. Really. But I can't really give a rating based on assumptions from other people's reviews. I keep coming back to this game, hoping to enjoy it a bit more but since I never get anywhere (probably spent around 6 hours of this game and it feels like I've taken a step into the game, then turned around and decided to observe that step for a long time... PS: Maybe the best way to enjoy the story in this game is to skip everything until you learn the mechanics more? I don't know...
Pretty good. Could use a central plot, not a "get from A to B. Go!" insentive.
Lovely made
I've had this for YEARS and I'm still playing this game. Highly recommend! (yes, it's hard... 😉)

'Out There' wants the player to feel as alone and empty as the protagonist, and the art design, soundtrack, writing, and gameplay all contribute brilliantly to this objective. At first glance, one might see the influence of 'FTL', but even one playthrough of 'Out There' will show otherwise. 'FTL' is frantic, but 'Out There' is an methodical odessey, recorded by the log kept by the main, and only, character. It's beautiful. I don't get to fully explain my love for the game in 500 words.

Love this game. So atmospheric. I've noticed an issue where closing the app can lose the last few turns, but that's not a big deal. It's like a roguelike - brutal at times but with hard work you learn how the game works and you're rewarded for it.

Really nice game with a lot of replay value. The chance to survive until one of the many different endings, manage resources better, learn + use new tech and just explore the full universe... Those are the drivers that kept me playing. The artwork is simple but nice too.
Super hard. Too much RNG. Could never beat the game, even after hours of practice.

Rng done in a really bad way. There are a number ways to make Rng feel less frustrating, uninteractive, and unfair. I hope devs could figure it out. In any case, there is definitely a problem in the way rng is handled in this game. This has little to do with game difficulty, or with the player's patience. Rng in this game makes the overall experience feel like a giant waste of time.
Fun game. But way too random and the bad random events are worse then the good ones. Also dimishing returns on any resources to mitigate the bad stuff.

I want to like it, but..Dispite the simplisity its plagued with bugs: multible ships' cargo overlaping, touches not registering, often probe returns 'blank slot', the list is LONG. Fix & add tap to select/move option & allow using resources from probe. Ill keep trying...
Several years later devs are not just supporting, but EVOLVING the game further!! Premium roguelike with scifi setting is a rare gem in the stores nowadays. This game is PRICELESS

Good concept but very frustrating to have to constantly worry over the consumption of your materials, where your going to find them next is anyone's guess, you definitely will have to have a random luck stream to get anywhere.
Game doesn't work anymore. SHAME
Fun and well written. There are definitely some runs where the odds are definitely against you, but the trip remains enjoyable none-the-less
There's a bug with the music and sound
One of the best games on the google play store: tricky, challenging, immersive and well-structured with a lot of endings and emotions to be felt.

Decent enough. I wanted this experience to be a lot of the FTL events with space exploration. It mostly delivers, but I found the interactions with the alien races is just too flat. Really detracts from an otherwise immersive game.
An absolutely fantastic game for passing time in a simulated universe
The game could be a fun adventure but it's far to random to be replayed repetitively no skill, all luck feels like a grind after a few play throughs
Pure RNG with little to no gameplay.

I would give it a five, but when I reached the red target system it did not unlock the red locked ship in the start of the next game. Reaching the red target just sends me to the green target. I had already finished the green ending and unlocked the green ship.
Good for any aspiring astronaut 😎

I'm so excited to see this updated for modern phones. They've also added a sort of new game+ content, where you can start with different ships than the base ship, plus some other stuff like mini quests.

Having died hundreds of times when you win i's a rewarding feeling. It put you through all the emotions but you come out better & smarter for it. Rogue-like is an understatement. Perma-death means the stakes are high from the start. You'll die a lot but if you learn from your mistakes you'll get there. It's not as random as it makes out to be. Brilliant game. The Omega version makes me want to replay. I would love a drop flag for black hole backtracking

It used to be a great game, I played it a year ago, but now there is a lot of bugs, especially when using the ship with 8 sphere in a square, and the switching of ships is also buggy, some equipment cannot be selected and dismantled
Cosmic, sad, and, well, out there. Keep pushing forward. Keep some space in your stores for Omega. Keep resting your luck.

The best space survival game I ve played so far. The intuitive and easy to learn game controls hides immersive gameplay coupled with an ethereal music score. The new Alliance addition has a tech update- cocoon, get this from rocky planets. With this in your ship, a cocoon ship emerges and gives you a second chance of survival wherever your character dies.
Addictive, unforgiving, and beautiful.

Great story and new update is awesome! Really like the new update. Of course there are some bugs, but they are minor. The main pros of the update are, different ships at start, and finding aliens on rocky planets. Really expands the game. The new orange ending is fun too. I've only found one alein to go there, but I am hopeful to see this ending completed soon.

The gameplay is resource and technology management with limited inventory space. But the events and the different endings transform into an epic survival saga among the stars. Great update to the game by the way.

UPDATE 02/12/20 Game has been updated and it no longer crashes. Moreover, new features added. Big thanks to the devs for keeping such a great game running. PREVIOUS Sad to give this game a bad review. This is an excellent, challenging, creative game that will give players many hours of entertainment. Unfortunately it has not been updated in years and (as of this review on pixel 3 on Android 10) is no longer running. It's a real shame because is one of the best mobile games ever.
Been playing this since 2014. Still getting new content. Appreciate the work gone into this...... One of my fave games. 👍

I really like this game for the story, graphics and atmosphere, but the inventory management required is such a massive detractor that i have to subtract 2 stars from this rating. It makes an otherwise fun experience painful. If constantly juggling far too few inventory slots is your kind of a challenge then this is the game for you. Also a bit buggy with the latest update. Sometimes i cannot interact with inventory when transferring cargo. Some slots will work, others won't.
I want to like this game bit can't. It's boring and repetitive. Pretty graphics and sound though.
The update made this game enjoyable.

This game is brilliant as it is but I've thought of some ways to improve it.     Please show the maintenance dock when probing or mining.     Create a 'Sanity' meter that will increase and decrease based on log entries and increase when the player encounters life on a planet.     Create a 'Fabricator' which uses 1 omega to produce a preset unchangeable amount of an element on board.     Create NPCs which act like another player. The player can orbit a planet it is orbiting and hail them. After hailing, a screen much like when the player orbits an abandoned ship will show, adding a 'Trade' dock and showing cargo automatically. If trade is agreed upon then the player and NPC places the elements in the trade dock and confirms trade, which moves the elements from the NPC's trade dock into the players cargo.     A multiplayer mode in which the other players are treated much the same as NPCs. The players orbits the same planet, hails and waits for the other player to accept or decline. When accepted they move to the trade screen but a chat system is added. Players agree on trade, place elements in trade dock and confirm.     Please make these available and thank you for a great game!
Not only have you updated the game (it now works on my new Xperia 1) but you've added a ton of free content AND added 21:9 support!!! Thank You!
On of the best sci fi exploration games out there. A real gem.
Great Game (-;
Another free update after years with it feeling complete yeah okay this game perfect

Great game, but frustrating. As others have stated, luck is a big part of the game. One may need a long string of good luck to get far... which may appeal to some, but also frustrate. Luck might extend into ways that might not seem "realistic", for example planets should often contain a much wider variety of available elements, so the involvement of luck often seems too punishing.
Not working on Pixel 4 anymore. I guess I can trash the app now as there won't be any update soon :( Update : works again :)
Thank you so much for the update for newer devices!
A new update, years later! Great developer.

I love the new update. Also, bug reports: - Human icon shows an alien instead. - In a random event I got an Alien item. It had no protrait, and I could split it (0 alien, 1 alien). The names were also random elements like Tungsten. - I cannot move items to expanded item space after the Symbiotic Extension upgrade. The game acts like I'm throwing things away. - When taking over ships I randomly can't interact with items. - Every once in a while I'll learn a word with no definition. "ATLAS = "

This is number 1 on my list of favorite mobile games of all time, my other two favorites being The Room and FTL. Excellent developers, extremely well created experience. I got this app before the release of Omega edition (the first major content update), and now I look forward to exploring even more through The Alliance update. Thank you, Mi-Clos Studio.
Great game !
Boring and repetitive. Nothing extraordinary about this game.
the game doesnt work on oneplus 7 pro which is a shame because it would look awesome.
Still amazing after all these years! Always something new when I come back. Thx guys! Great work!
Super fun and the update looks great!
A prendre sans hésiter une seconde. De plus le jeu a été mis a jour récemment après plusieurs années de disponibilité ! Qui fait ça? C'est fantastique. Merci beaucoup au développeur.
Excellent resource gathering game with great graphics and captivating story. I feel however that the RNG is much more unforgiving than it needs to be.
Lovely. When you figure out how to succeed the game is made simpler, but there's always more to find. An excellent experience. Don't give up.
Great game fun to play. The latest update is great
Game has a new update fixed my problem loving the new icon
This is nice and interesting game. I have spent a lot of hours playing this. Rendering me Space Rangers
...really bad update - crashes on launch. Wouldn't suggest buying this right now, better wait for a fix.
OMG! Such an amazing adventure game! Congratulations for this incredible project! This game definitely deserve a lot of awards!

I can't wait to dive into Alliance! Such a great game with so much replayability. I have enjoyed this game so much, and have it on all platforms I own (Android, iOS, PC). It's especially good when you are on flights or stuck waiting for something, as it's engaging and does not burn up your data. Thank you Mi Clos! You all rock. Ç'est très bien!
They did update it!

*edit* works again on on ui 2 Great game. On a note10plus now it freezes at game start. Have to reboot phone uninstall reinstall. It's getting annoying. *edit* another week unplayable moving to uninstall soon.
The game doesnt work on new phones.
Great fun

only recommended for experienced strategy game enthusiasts who care nothing to graphics and demand pure gameplay interactions..the sweet spot is that it always give you the '' I'm going to die'' feeling even if you are one step before the game end....the omega edition made it even better
Update: Still a great game, but it freezes most of the time on my Oneplus 7 Pro.
Did not work with my Samsung galaxy s10 plus. Wish I read the reviews before I downloaded this game.

This game is completely pot luck. The only skill in the game is trying to rearrange the materials you need but only when it gives it to you. Just when you think you are managing, bam! It hits you with something that ends the game. Nearly £4 for a game that involves going to a star system collecting minerals and most importantly fuel (which can be a right joke) and trying to get back to earth. Don't waste your money unless the price goes down to £1
Freezes immediately on the title screen. Galaxy s10+
Alas, it worketh no more as of the last update on a Note 10+. Still a great game for older tablets and such however.

As many other reviews have stated, this game is outdated on the mobile version. It no longer posts or records achievements. If you do not care about the achievements but love this type of game, you can still play it offline as a time-killer. I bought this app a long time so I do not regret purchasing it although I do miss getting the achievements.
One of the just mobile games!

Great game. Challenging and lots of content. Even on easy its very difficult. This is because your winning the game is based solely on luck. Loot from drills and probes is very inconsistent, certain materials are needed to progress and if you dont get them by the second solar system the third will be your last. The main problem is space for carrying items. There just isnt enough at the start. I love this game but i fear i will never know what happens at the end.
Great strategy game

Loved Out There for its great story, beautiful visuals, and peak roguelike mechanics. Got a new phone (Samsung Galaxy S10+) and now it freezes on the homescreen. Unfortunate for how much I want to keep playing this.

As many other reviews have stated, this game has not been updated in years and crashes on newer hardware. Samsung galaxy s10 +, game freezes immediately on title screen, music continues to play but screen is completely frozen and unresponsive.
Good little time waster... Good atmospheric music.
Game keeps crashing. S10. Will only load the main screen and then crash. Locking phone.
Game no longer works, crashes on start up - leaving music playing in the background until you force quit the app.

A well written and interesting game that constantly kills you and forces you to restart. Extremely frequent no-win scenarios. During a recent playthrough, I died from lack of oxygen because I never encountered a planet that had oxygen. Basically it's super random and you have to get super lucky to win. Annoying.

Insanely addictive, deceptively complex and unexpectedly challenging! If you like rogue like, upgrades and a genuine strategy with some really challenging gameplay this is probably for you. I spent ages toying with the idea of paying for a game like this, I'm glad I did! It's rare you find a game these days without micro transactions even at a premium price. The worldbuilding is excellent and the story is intriguing, I can genuinely see myself coming back to this time and time again.
On my Note 10+, freezes every time on the title screen
Every time I try to launch the game it locks up on my new Note 10+. Need a refund please.
The game loaded to title screen and then nothing, it didn't register any touches to any icon...
Never got to play the game because it freezes 2 seconds into the loadscreen...
game is crashing on startup. the music continues to play, but the screen is frozen and completely unresponsive.

I love the game, when I can play it . The screen wants to freeze when I load it. Using a note 10+ this this game locks up. Touch screen and no response . Trying to continue leads to black screen and once again no response. I feel like I wasted my money.
The game is extremely addicting and i have still yet to get bored of it... Great game idea!!!!
Used to play this all the time, but now I cant get past the start screen.
What an awesome experience! What else can I say about a game that locks up 2 seconds into the title screen other than way to drop the ball developers! 🖕
Très clairement le jeu mobile le plus incroyable et immersif auquel il m'ait ete donné de jouer !
Pretty awesome mobile game if you like resource management and choice and consequence

Great concept, but lacks depth and progression. Luck is 70% of every run even on easy, you have to learn different languages but when you die all that progression goes in the trash. You lose everything after a run, which for some games is fine but in a space explorer game is a fun killer for me.

In short this is a dark, story driven adventure game with a heavy emphasis on resource management. Of the few dozen games Ive played on Mobile, this is my favorite. Its not a free game but it is worth the money. No microtransactions or "pay to win" type gameplay. Its a complete game with several endings depending on the path you choose. The galaxy is randomly generated each time, which makes some sessions harder than others depending on the hand you get dealt.

Offline, challenging resource manager and exploration game. Casual players might find it frustrating to progress, but once the basics are learnt you'll start to gain your way. 4 stars for repetition over attempts, but solid nonetheless.
After a while the game gets boring so if you happen to have a friend that already has the game then ask hime to let you play a bit to see if you are willing to buy the game.
One of my favourite games ever.

It is a fun and challenging game. In the beginning you keep losing a couple of times. But when you get the hang of it, you can fly the galaxy without problems. You need to think smart and efficient. Lots of things can be improved though. There are quite many bugs still, I got stuck while traveling through a wormhole and a story opened twice, after which the invisible buttons stayed. And when you accidentally click on give up, there is no turning back :(

• NO PROCGEN MAP AS ADVERTISED: actually same exact galaxy, every time. How did they screw this up?! • "300+ choices stories" but get ready for the same two dozen or so over & over again. • Save is messed up. What planet you orbit doesn't get saved, but what star system you are in does? Why? And sometimes you come back to find changes you made to your tech (rearrangement) have reverted, while your supplies are still as you left them. How did they mess THIS up?!?! • Otherwise sorta O.K.-ish?

I have a feeling you guys did not even test it. Day 400, out of all the modules I have - my engine dies after standard travel for 14 fuel. I have not been making any discussions, no encounters at all. Out of nowhere - game over. The planets in the star system are all occupied by the enemy, so I can't get any recourses to fix it. The hell? A sudden death mechanic. For no reason. You might aswell have had shown me a picture of your balls instead. Would have the same experience.
years since i last played but still one of, if not the best mobile game i've ever played

The phrase "more than meets the eye" could not fit this game more perfectly. On the surface, a simple, proceedurally generated space travel game, where you need to get from point A to point B managing items and resources as you go. But it's the encounters you have as you travel that really make it interesting, you can pick up bits of alien languages to help you deal with future encounters, abandond your ship for a better one, or collapse a star to destroy a solar system to name a few, great fun.

I don't usually go for mobile games, but this one is really enjoyable. It has a loosely told story, though the real seller is the survival. It can be frustrating to see about 2 hours, and 60 star systems worth of progress end because of chance, but that's part of the game, though It is still doable. The music and art style is really well done, and sets a haunting tone for the game. It's not action based, but if you don't mind a slow burn and a challenge, you'll enjoy it.
amazing game. the story is out of this world. poor guy
frustratingly difficult

Currently unable to probe for fuel, an essential element in playing this game for more than 3 minutes! On a Samsung Note 8, fully updated. I don't think developers are keeping up with their product anymore, so I'm going to say pass on this.

Rarely would I leave a recommendation but this game is by far at the top of my list. if you're a fan of space, survival and adventure then you should love this game. I finally managed to finish one of the endings on easy after 13 hours and will play more to complete other possible endings. Hope for so much from this company using the same universe. Could even see this as a 2D Eve online type of experience with additional content.
this game is pretty cool. good artwork decent gameplay
I'm not able to connect the game with play games, when i press the button nothing happens.
Amazing.
Too complex to play. Missing a good tutorial
Excellent story and awesome artwork !! This game is worth every single penny.
update to pie os please
I don't know kinda boring
great game, menus can be a bit frustrating though

The best game i have ever played on a mobile device. The theme music fits the game perfectly, i love the gameplay, pure strategy and resource replenishment, interaction with the alien life forms, gaining technologies, etc. great job developer!!!

a solid mobile game, mostly a choose-your-own-adventure with a slight emphasis on placing modules inside your ship. not incredibly engaging, but it's really nice for long flights. distraction friendly. besides getting a visual indicator that you have been to a star already, no information is saved from where you've been and you cannot make notes.

Great game, alot to discover, only issue is that I can only play it on one phone as it doesn't save your progress on Google games (it's not working at all with it, the button doesn't do anything). Hope it gets fixed.

Great game. Doesn't work anymore. Not sure what update killed it, but it boots into black screen after logos and does nothing. Sometimes freezes during logos. Never makes it to main menu. Device is a Galaxy S10+ Uninstalled, rebooted, and reinstalled. Fixed the problem.
Great game but why in the world would an explorer not keep notes of exactly what's on each planet he explores??? It's nuts that there is no functionality for that!
Fantastic game, difficult but always fun. Every playthrough is different than the last. I keep coming back to this game.
very hard but engaging scifi rogue like. highly recommend
Might be one of the hardest games I ever played. Totally captivating, worth every cent! 5 stars

It's a good fun game but it has issues. Hasn't been updated or changed in anyway in years. Everything is random so you can't plan ahead meaning you can easily lose a run through no fault of your own and have to start all over again. The nature of RNG. In all the years I've owned this game and played on Normal, I have never been able to complete a run because of the RNG. Thats what makes this game frustrating. If you don't care about that then you may still have a good time.

Don't get me wrong, I love this game. I am just so upset that the ACHIEVEMENTS DON'T WORK, especially after finishing the most difficult ending and realizing that fact. Once that small issue is addressed, then this will be a 5 star review instead. The music is great, the story is interesting and enigmatic. I would still suggest buying this game, for sure.
pretty damn hard, but enjoyable nonetheless
It's a great game
A mystery that I keep wanting to explore and learn more. A great way to kill time on trips or between classes.
great soundtrack.

Excellent game in the same vein as Weird Worlds minus the combat. I do wish the high score system was improved so that information about the high scoring run (or multiple if possible) was recorded. It would be nice to be able to review exactly what I did in my high scoring run. The game is very well polished in all areas and is certainly worth the price of admission. Very replayable.
great scifi, love the design choices and difficulty level
Great game
Very difficult space survival game but has plenty of replay value.
meh, not for me.
The Android 9 update on my s8 killed the game. It loads upto the point it should be at the main screen and then it black screens you! Devs please help!
This game is one of the best I've played. Difficult, and different every time! A must play!!!!
one of my favorite games def top 3 on all platforms

FTL like game tho VERY simplified and with some substantial flaws like dead end parts with non-reachable solar systems, too little space on ship for both cargo and equipment. Some things they did right, like sorry, events/choises, alien dialogues with gradual translation.

You can go to almost the middle of the game which can take 2 to 3 hours of your life and do a wrong turn loose material then your dead and have to start all over again FROM THE BEGINING. Please create some sort of saving point...this game is fun but you get very bored with having to restart every time.
FTL but a bit different. Quick and fun. Great music too!
Challenging game with a balance between strategy and luck. Some paths that you took in the galaxy withoit the proper navigation instruments could be an dead end.
Unplayable black screen
i love space travel games. there could be some battle events but still it is very interesting
Please add auto text read feature. Introduce modes where its allowed to save progress
This isnt just a simple Game This is an Experience The Soundtrack is just beautiful
This game is great! Super easy to learn, but very hard to get good at. Each attempt builds the world that you are exploring with 4th wall breaks and unnerving philosophical implications.
would give stars if the achievements worked lol doesn't connect to google play games

I think this is a cool game so far. My only problem is that I got stuck on a couple of stars because of a random event. I've just started and the small radius of the starting ship couldnt reach the other stsrts. I soon ran out of fuel to gather then met with a gameover screen. Kinda unfair…
Got it free
It has the most incredible atmosphere. With the calculation and risk taking lends a satisfying desperation. I bought the original version, and bought the new one as well.
Great game now doesn't load. Honor v10. Played it and finished it. Since last update will not load past logo screens shame as its good and would like to replay! Edit: reinstalled and it works.
really great, cant beat it though ;/
Yes. Yes. Yes.

I love the FTL style adventure and all... But when ever I run out of fuel IN THE TANK (to make things clear) but have plenty in the cargo hold it still forces me to end the game... A game braking problem that is illogical... The protagonist signs off saying there he doesn't have anything to top off the tank? Even if I have 2-3 stacks of fuel? Or an omega or 2... Beautiful and psychotically difficult; from a gamer who lavishes a challenge, from a plethora of AAA titles and obscure indie games, this game could have been a milestone for the latter category but is, sadly, little more than a depression simulator. The art and narrative are top notch, but more than 90% of the content will never be seen by anyone except those with an inordinate amount of time on their hands. Watching LPs completely spoils discovering the otherwise brilliant allure of the game for yourself, and it really is a shame, given the vast potential it may have otherwise had...and there isn't anything else like it in terms of design. FTL doesn't count at all. Failing literally within the starting system over and over before you get the hang of the fact that there really is only one way to success leaves a bitter taste that ruins the captivating effect the rest game has, and the fun of it is eclipsed by this. Eventually succeeding doesn't give you a sense of accomplishment - you feel like you've been through a frustrating ordeal and with the sudden ending, there's zero reward or replayability. Too bad I can't recommend this at all. I really, really wanted to.  Would be much better with a companion comic or animated miniseries...maybe then it would emerge from its unfortunate obscurity. The Chronicles series looks interesting, but I don't know if they have the same teeth-pulling, frustrating artificial difficulty, so I'm avoiding those until I can somehow find out.

Reviewing this after I finally beat it. This is a very difficult resource management game. Beginning tips for players:  1. Conserve your fuel. Think small, jump small, mine/probe small, and always have a reserve. HE gives you more fuel than H - keep that in mind. 2. Switch ships often where it makes sense. Be aware that not all ships use HE and H for fuel. 3. The Omega element you receive from aliens can be applied to any repair or category of resource.   Great game. I wish there was a little more customization with the ships though, eg choosing your starting ship.

Loneliness, fear and death. Out There has a lot of these things, but it's so much more than that. It's a resource management sim with a surprising emotional resonance, where one bad decision or careless mistake can leave your corpse drifting in deep space for all eternity, yet a stroke of luck or desperate gamble can get you that much closer to home. It's hard, but I feel that in being hard it reflects the vastness and wonder - and, sometimes, the sheer existential horror - of the universe. The lovely comic book art and wonderfully atmospheric music only reinforce that. Essential.

There's a difference between "challenge" and "luck," and this game is weighted heavily toward the latter. It resembles FTL with a rogue-like space theme, but lacks the depth FTL possesses with decision trees concerning crew/salvage/systems management. Lacking crew management at all, where salvage or systems management is concerned the player has a little control but to roll the dice on whatever actions they can take and hope for the best. After a game of FTL you can recall certain decisions you made that potentially cost you the game, but Out There really just leaves you saying "better luck next time" that's really unsatisfying ("I have no way of knowing, so I'll just hope this system I'm travelling to has a planet with fuel, and that the planet is worth mining. No? Game over - oh well, guess I'll repeat this until the stars line up").   Tl;dr don't play if you're not a fan of games based on a lot of luck. Do play if you're looking to burn some time and don't mind repeating actions over hoping for different results.

Some games are hard because they want to be challenging. Out There is hard because the game is so short that it doesn't want you realize you've wasted your money. To put this in perspective, there is a marker indicated once you're mid way across the galaxy. That is where the game has its hugely, unsatisfying and anti climactic ending. Skill is less of a factor here compared to blind luck, under the right conditions you can finish the game in 30 mins. Don't spend money on this trash. I would have warned other people earlier but I just finished a run for the first time despite playing off and on for over a year. Here some advice, stock up on nothing but fuel from the start and don't explore unless you have an almost full cargo of fuel. Keep iron on hand in case of repairs tho.

I want to like this game more than I do. The art is nice, the music is great, and the idea is good. But the gameplay feels like my choices don't really matter and I'm just hoping to get lucky.   Did you end up going down a dead end? Pretty much game over. Keep flying to systems with no fuel to harvest? Pretty much game over. Random event happened that erased all of your technology? Wow fun.  A lot of the game just feels like hoping the map likes you and you can find fuel and keep going. Every system is the same basic principle. Rocky plants have metals, gas planets have fuel. You visit a system, visit a planet, and harvest. Rinse repeat and hope you can get enough fuel, oxygen, and iron at each stop to maintain your ship.  Other than that there's not much strategy or choice. The game is "hard" in the sense that it's rare you find enough stuff along the way to keep you going. Not hard in the sense that you can make choices to really help you. Sometimes it feels like the game might as well just tell me right away if I won or lost.   I really don't feel like I do much in this game. I want to make it to the end, but there's not really that much you can do to help do that.

Under a seemingly beautiful package resides a very flawed experience. The game actively relies on random events outside of player's control, which turns Out There's amazing narrative into a repetitive flow of uninspired routine. The gameplay aspect is limited and boring, while the narrative does not progress properly because each step is a coin-toss, sometimes specifically aimed at ending the player's game. A shame that such a beautiful sci-fi story falls victim to a badly thought-out game.

I'm amazed. So far this is the best mobile game I've ever played. It borrows from one of my favourite 'roguelike' titles (Faster Than Light), but instead of copying, focuses more on the storytelling and micromanagement. Hellishly addictive and immersive. This is an example of game design done right: every element adds nicely to the game, no unnecessary gimmicks, and the whole format fits perfectly on a mobile platform. It also has a nice nostalgia factor - somehow it reminds me of a few titles I played on Amiga, and some other titles I enjoyed, but never to the point that it breaks immersion, just that nice, familiar feeling. Awesome job, waiting for more from you!

I had got one of the 4 endings within a few hours of playing. It was addictive enough to keep me going this long. Good way to spend an evening. Contrary to other reviews, this game is not really "difficult" or "hard". The skills and strategies you need to develop are not that complicated. The game is based on luck and once you have grasped the relatively simple concepts involved, it is luck which will determine if you live or (much more frequently) die.  It's luck what resources you mine, it's luck what technology you get given, it's luck what ship upgrades you come across, it's luck that decides if a critical component is going to randomly fail somewhere where you cannot build a replacement. You can't use skill to work your way through these mishaps. If you don't get the good luck, you fail.  Still quite compulsive, though, but I would prefer it to be "hard" because you have to think things through rather than "hard" merely because the odds are stacked against you.

I think this is somewhere between an oldschool serious roguelike and what most people expect now from an Android game. I love the concept AND the execution, but I think it's clear from many of the reviews that it's not something a lot of people are really expecting right now.  This is a tough game, and once you play through a few times it's clear there's a limited amount of non-randomly-generated material that becomes a little repetitive, but in my opinion that's not a big deal. I do appreciate the quality, humor, and insight that went into the written work, but it does kind of put the game in a difficult middle ground between a pure random dungeon and a graphic novel.  Overall I'm impressed with, happy with, and inspired (as a developer) by this game. I'm glad I spent the cash on it, but I'm conceding a star simply because it does stumble a bit by pushing a very limited amount of custom scenario in an otherwise randomly-generated environment.

(Example: you need technology to upgrade your equipment but you have no way to influence what you get, if you get anything at all.  Land on a mineral planet and you might get a tech.  Probably won't.  The depth of the game is choosing to land on the rocky planet or not.)  Overall, the quality of the game is good, though it could use some UI improvements like zoom-able map. There are some games that walk a fine line between pure gaming and pure art, and this is one of them. The art and the music are beautiful, and the astronaut's logs a very compelling read that really draws you in. On the gaming side, the mechanics are not very complex but understanding how to survive truly is a challenge. I confess I don't really appreciate the whole roguelike philosophy of being too cool for savepoints, and would have probably given up without a little savescumming; if you quit and restart, everthing you did in the solar system you're currently on is not saved, which helps get to the sweet spot where it's not excessively frustrating while still instilling the fear of losing. With no in-app purchases and a fantastic experience, the only thing missing is more gaming depth, but these days you don't really see big, long games with this kind of quality on mobile which aren't ports of older games that used to cost fairly more than they now do back when they were first released for the PC.  TL;DR beautiful, captivating, frustrating, worth it.

I'm still dipping my toes into the iOS/Android market of indie games, but Out There is the only one I've played that has brought about, if not tears, then a kind of soft disquiet in me. As you do your best to keep the little man in your spaceship alive, you get to know him in his journal entries. He's not special in any way - he's his own person, with his flaws, his bitterness, his hope and his longing. I've reached two endings already, and I'm hoping to reach the third - even if I've already spoiled myself on it via Youtube.  This is posthuman science fiction at its finest, and I've never seen a game that has tackled the tropes and themes as succesfully as this game does. It's the deeper, more meditative variant of FTL - you're not fighting a war against a rebel alliance, you're fighting a war within the void of interstellar travel, and with yourself. A true shining star amongst an otherwise compromised market of games that are  riddled with free-to-play frivolity.

Several times I have used the last of my fuel to travel to a place I thought might let me get more fuel such as a beacon or garden planet. I didn't get a chance to try though, it just told me game over before I could make contact with the aliens to see if they give omega or click on the beacon.
Love the challenge wish it was more like ftl
An amazing game that really challenges you in a good way to keep you wanting to try again and get ever further then before
Absolutely love this game. So many freaking hours of gameplay... You can try all you want but visiting every star is a major challenge. Can't wait for the new version... Merci Mi-Clos!
I love this game.
Best game ever

While it's a game that has few shortcomings (being one-time-play for example) it has very interesting mechanics. I would suggest to add story mode for players who want to explore more of the galaxy instead of desperately scrambling for resources.  But it has great concept, re playability and visuals. 5/5!

Very well made game. Just check spelling and lower the amount of random things breaking, it gets pretty ridiculous when your engine blows up four times in a row. A strategy and smart playing both get trashed by constant, random disaster. A save function would be nice as well.
Great game. Hard, challenging, making you scream in despair as you run out of oxygen. Best space themed game on Google Play!
Hard and fun

As said by others, this game is hard and punishes mistakes. Nevertheless, that's where the challenge lies!  My only gripe is that, after many failed attempts, I finally arrived at one of the target planets and the game just ends after a bit of a cut scene with no option to play on which i would have liked to do

Amazing game. I am completely addicted! My problem is that I always get far and then lose.  It used to be I got a little farther each time but I seem to have found my limit. Please add some sort of difficulty control! Preferably with usage/availability of resources. I understand the game is supposed to be challenging, and it is. But its very merciless and id like to be able to get farther in the game.
Reminds me of some wonderful games from my childhood.  Would be nice to be able to save periodically.
A very challenging game. Frustrating at times. A game on resource management.
For those who love a good challenge, this game certainly delivers! A well made sci-fi game with interesting writing and a cool atmosphere.
It's different.  I don't know about "dark", but different. At first I was a little put off by not being able to save my progress, but that's what gives the game it's challenge. Worth the $5.
Ironically, as soon as I achieved this, the game promptly ended. No "keep playing" option?
Absolutely Epic...
Boring
Sweet hardcore sci-fi fun!
Great but no save feature, still hours and hours of fun
All the strategy of FTL without the battle tactics (shame). Brilliant atmosphere and execution. If you like challenging strategy with high replayability, get this game.
Real tough. Makes for lots of play. Great art.

Nintendo hard is a good description I saw from another review.... Too many people complaining the game is too hard - they're definitely not from the NES generation where that was what made a game worth playing. It's a great game, it is hard, but you won't get bored trying to beat it. Don't hesitate to buy.

Just get this through your head: you'll die in this game... a lot. But that's part of the charm: you need to start fragile and learn what tech you need to make it through. I just beat the game and I have to admit, it felt a bit TOO hard at first but I beat it once I stopped worrying about dying and instead focused on learning what worked, and what didn't.  Very enjoyable game, well worth it. If you like strategy games, this is an obvious buy.

Game seems like it's going to be solid and well designed.  But, the first thing i'm noticing in the tutorial is broken English in the text. This has me reading the same thing over trying to understand what the author is trying to tell me in the text tutorial.  It's a inconvience, but not a game changer thus far.  Just a annoyance.  Will report ba k after i have more time with this game.
Good game to kill time. Have to really be lucky.
Read above
Best Android game I have played
I ran my phone from 97% to dead playing this game! It's that much fun!
Pretty pretty pretty good.

This game can be infuriating! The art is beautiful, the concept great, with that quantum leap "next leap make take you home" mentality. I would love to see some sort of freeplay mode where you could go back two or three decisions.  I think that could keep me playing longer.  After MANY missions I don't think I'm even close to home! Overall a fun game. Four stars for now... Could be five with some tweaks.
This game is very hard but addicting. I love the narration!

I've been looking for a game like this forever. It has a point and click element to it but it is so much more. This is a an intense strategy game, created in a randomized universe, with so much depth,  I rarely encounter the same reading twice. I like to think of it like Star Trek Voyager in a more realistic sense. You awake from a stasis chamber only to find yourself lost in space. Equipped with limited resources and a small cargo hold, you try to find a way back to earth without dying or becoming stranded

A painful addiction that is only leading me to harm and death. This game is brutal and all your work can be undone it just one move. However, this very challenge is what drives me to keep playing. It's frustrating in the best way possible.
Okay, I really like this game a whole lot. It's not as good as FTL, but it's a good mobile version. Id loooooove if they'd add a little more spice to it.
This is a must have. Its worth paying for.

This is a great strategy game. You must choose very carefully what technologies & resources you use on your ship, as well as which planets you visit. HOWEVER chance/luck plays such a big part of how far you get - and there are no save points. Its quite frustrating if you've spent several hours on one game to get wiped out by bad luck  & have to start back at the beginning again. PLEASE ADD SAVE POINTS - EVEN JUST ONE OR TWO - TO GET 5* REVIEW.

I'm a huge fan of sci-fi, and I've recently been getting into rougelikes, so when a heard about Out There, I had to check it out. If you've played FTL, this game shares similarities in exploration and progression through ship upgrades. But while FTL focuses on combat, Out There completely eschews it for resource management. If you're a fan of space settings, rougelikes, and more patient strategy games, you'll love Out There. If not, you'll at least agree that the art, music, and atmosphere is fantastic.
the stupid random events turns this almost great strategy game into a dumb lucky shot game.
เกมแนวภาษา+strategy ฉากจบมีหลายแบบ ดนตรีแจ่ม ซื้อมาช่วงลดราคาก็เกินคุ้ม
Incredible replay value.

Hop from star to star scraping enough resources from the planets to keep your ship running.   Sprinkled with Sci-Fi flavor, this survival game is all about failing, and that innate desire to try again.  Procedurally generated maps, and randomized events keeps you coming back for more punishment.  The language translation has some misspellings and grammatical errors.  This, coupled with less than stellar ending earns Out There a 4/5.
Addictive and challenging
Unique and well written game
Favorite game of all time. Hands down.
Addicting in the way all mobile games should be, easy to pick up, hard to put down

Superb game, with hours of game-play to be had! I've been waiting for a game like FTL to be released on android and this is the closest comparison yet!!! It has its own style and the artwork and audio completes this game nicely.

Awesome, creative and strategic and also good on battery life. This game is nice looking and there are hardly even load times, if your wanting a game that is fun,  good on battery and statigic buy this game now!
Awesome app it is easy to fail in this game but it's easy to learn from your mistakes
Cool strategy, story, and dialog. Definitely worth the price!
Love it!!!!
Simple polished space adventure. Great style graphics, great atmosphere of lonelness. Different each time you play it. No glitches yet, runs asfast as you can push icons on galixy note 10.2
Too hard and i love it.
A well paced and difficult challenge. Combined with a good story and intriguing interactions it makes a great game. It's almost a rogue like choose your own adventure but so much more.
I don't say this about many games, but this was infuriatingly addictive. Just one more go addictive
Buy it
Awesome gameplay. At least 6h needed to finish the main scenario, plus Achievment I could play this game for DAYS ! Amazing story.
Pretty awesome game. Challenging and fun however without save option can be frustrating. Overall great game, good job developers but I do think its a tad overpriced... Just saying.
Tons of replay value, difficult enough to keep coming back for more

It's very frustrating to not be able to see where you've been and what the systems you've visited contain. If I've been there, I should know they have! I should also be able to look back at my journey and not be limited to the current range of the scanner. Fix those things and I'll rate more highly.
The game's learning curve way seem steep at first, but stick with it and you will be rewarded. Tons of strategy, replay value, and fun.

An absolutely wonderful app. You can just pick up and play. It's incredibly addictive. Regardless of the perma-death, this game keeps me coming back again and again. I have poured hours and hours into this game and I haven't reached the end yet, but that is so not a deterent. This is a beautifully realistic scifi adventure. Each trip is different and enticing. Choose carefully, it's a wonderful, spiritual, mystical universe Out There.
One thing I dont like is that u can make all this progress but if u run fuel u have to restart the whole game its not fair and ive bern trying to learn the aliens language but it is randomized

After the first 2 time of playing it I felt I knew what to do and on the 3rd try I got to the farthest I ever got in my first 2 tries. I had to backtrack a few times and in this game fuel is important so that meant I had quite a lot of fuel but I still ran out.                 I forgot how long I was playing this because I was so focused on what to do, and what to pick. (because whatever you pick might kill you) but all the random scenarios are so cool! I only had the same one once I think? Out of 40+?
Then you'll like this. Guaranteed. Galaxy s3.

I haven't played a game quite like this before. It was a really neat game mechanic with lots of different strategies for play. A little bit of a learning curve, but I think games don't do that anymore, and they should. I wish that the game had a little more documentation on some of the ship upgrades, but you can have totally different play experiences each time from different strategies or sheer luck. A+++++ would download again!!!
Installed this awhile ago,  just started playing and I can not put it down
+story +replayablility  Omega edition - when?
Just get it. It's so hard, but when you finally figure something out you feel like a genius.
Difficult but incredibly fun game. Graphics and soundtrack make for an immersive experience.
Great game, great idea, but underdeveloped! I can't continue when I finish the game, to discover new technologies and improve on my ship! Otherwise, very challenging and amazing game!
I am out there, no time to write review.
Simply an amazing game.

Only annoying thing is if I'm out of iron and my engine blows up usually the only way to fix it is by dismantling my drill and the only way to get more iron is my drill so as soon as that happens you're almost always screwed.
Great difficult game. I like the theme and challenge.
Cruel games that consume lots of time cant afford showstopper bugs.
Ótimos gráficos, jogabilidade desafiante e muito divertido
Multiple endings. All of which are hard to get.

It's like playing 'The Star Diaries' by Stanisław Lem: it's funny, it's atmospheric, and it's very interesting. A bit buggy, but I hope developers are working on bugs. So, I'd like to say thank you for the great product!
Awesome game similar to ftl.
This is big chalange.. Very hard and  cool game
I have played this non-stop for days and I can't get tired of it, nicely done!

Well written and thought provoking, while near perfectly balanced for challenge. Haunting music and even more haunting choices. I hope this starts a trend in mobile games - great substance and graphic design!
Amazing soundtrack and great procedural universe. Maybe I don't look hard enough but this is only the second mobile game I've found worth playing.
Feels just like those older create your own adventure books, with great audio and good visuals

Yeah, it's hard.  It's random. You have to play 30 or 40 times to beat it, and you have to get lucky too.  (Luck plays less of a role after a certain point.) Why does everyone seem to want games they win after the first couple of tries? What sense of accomplishment do you get from watching a game win itself?
Frustrating, yet rewarding.
Wow

Finally another game for gamers and not just a bloated money grab; there are far too many of those at the moment.  I think you'll like this game if you enjoy a good challenge.  If you feel a sense of accomplishment by making it just that much further in a difficult game where the choices you make have consequences (including the loss of some progression) then youll like Out There.  If you prefer having a win handed to you while the game spoon feeds you, keep looking.

One of the best mobile games out there. Decently good story line, but really brings back all those hours I spent in Oregon trail just revamped and in space! Even runs great on my old galaxy tab. Thank you for the game!
Excellent planet hopping exploration game!
The nonlinear storytelling and randomized encounters make the game challenging, but they also make it unique and exciting. It's worth every penny and every moment of your time.
Love it
Dont pick the green ending
I play this game as an apk before and have to accepted that this game is hard, but if you play this game with your experience and some luck you will achieve this game.

A true roguelike, in space!  It's hard, you've been warned: dying is half the experience. If you can't handle it, take your time and relax.    But I have a problem; isn't the game supposed to keep track of the words I translated from game to game? Cause it isn't the case.. Did I misinterpreted the message I received or is there a bug out there? ;)

Great game and concept. Super fun and the challenge givee you real satisfaction when you manage to explore all of the endings. My only complaint is that it is a little formulaic. Get the biggest ship, manage your resources and plan ahead for your destinations and you can just run around forever.
Excellent concept and execution
Love this game but it is really difficult, I know it's meant to be hard but having a save option or an easy mode would be awsome.
This game has everything needed to be awesome, except that it's way too hard: success depends entirely on chance, not on skill or attention to detail. Too much randomness makes for a bad game, IMO.
Very addictive, combining elements of roguelike and space exploration.

You cuss and claw and scratch. You make one wrong choice, one poor prioritization and it is over. I couldn't be more happy with 4 bucks I forked over, and I am quick to hit refund button over the slightest thing.

Out There is an excellent strategic space adventure, with simple but effective visuals and a grim but delightfully imaginative tone to its writing and ideas. Some do not enjoy the game's ruthless challenge and the crushing failures that can lead to but believe me, if you're persistent and learn from those failures(and with a little luck) you'll succeed. If you like science fiction and strategy and want a mobile game with depth and challenge look no further, just buy Out There.
Cracking game.
Excellent resource management game hidden in a wistful sci-fi explorer
I keep re-reviewing this game for one simple reason. Its atmospheric perfection.. just give the game a shot.

Don't be fooled by reviews this game is almost nothing like FTL.  This game is almost purely resource management and that's it's problem. You will often go several systems without finding any of a key resource, so you die. Or you travel a third of the galaxy and don't find any new technology so you get trapped in a dead end and die.  Unlike FTL there is rarely a lesson in a death, it feels like there was nothing you could have done to avoid it.  Some tweaking could make this game much better.
Really like the game, almost similar to FTL on pc. Hard, but that's the whole point! Well done devs :)
Its an awesome twist to strategy, even if you make the right decisions you wont get far by playing it safe :)
Game is great. Challenging. Which is why it's awesome. Takes a lot of time and patience, has great mechanics, and really cool story
Seriously if you are marking this down because it is hard then you should have read the description. It's an amazing strategic game and a high recommendation
Hard to master, I would add a difficulty level to it.
Seriously well done.  Great immersion!  Would love to see a sequel or add-on.
Love it
Every attempt and getting "home" is different... most repetitive games get boring so quickly... this is not that kind of game. well thought out and well executed!
One of the finest games I have ever played.
Atmospheric with a dry sense of humour.
Out There is hands down one of my favorite current games.  Creative problems solving is absolutely neccesary.  Very fun.
The game is just way too random to be any fun... the game gets very repetitive, very fast
lots of fun and replability.
Wonderfully challenging

With all the "impossible to lose" games out there it's great to play a challenging game. Out There has a roguelike difficulty (well, maybe a little easier) where the fun is in replaying it after dying and learning more every time.  As an added bonus, the soundtrack and writing are awesome, so it's a really immersive experience. Play it with headphones and read all the text! It's worth it.
Great but brutally difficult
Awesome!
At the point I reached I ran into a big monster and he told me that it is my destiny to save the human race then id big letters it said the end
Played a lot of this awsome game and Never the same play through. Kinda hard at first but lots of fun

One of the few games that keep me looking on google play,  between the crazy random events and the sense of customization along with the sense of exploration,  accompanied by the sense of apprehensions as you jumps,  possibly for the last time,  to a new star system,  you can't put this game down,  while lax on the action department the adventure will more than make up for it. This game is worth the money people,  worth more than what an extra turn on some candy crush bs is,  get this game, you won't regret
Great fun, atmospheric and challenging. The writing, however, is awful. Perhaps it needed a better translator, as it doesn't read like properly composed English.

Not easy, not complicated, but certainly complex in its simplicity and challenging in spades. The tutorial doesn't cover everything though, so be prepared to experiment a little when unfamiliar things happen.
Gets a bit repetitive and fuel limitation is way too irksome...
Very fun and addictive. Well worth the expense.
Pretty difficult

This is a great choose your own-adventure/rogue-like.  The gameplay/mechanics are slow-paced, revolving around resource management, but the unique story and events of each play-through makes it interesting each time.  Which is good because you will die horribly and alone multiple times and will have to start from scratch, really capturing the hopelessness of being stranded in space light-years from your solar system.
A stripped down FTL, love the tone and execution.

Interesting game that offer a different experience.  It kept me hooked for some 20hrs but i must say it becomes repetitive at some point and i didn't got through all the scenarios. Still a very good game.
Not unlike a throw back to the games of the late 80's and 90's they lean heavy on good writing and choices for game play. Really well made, even the soundtrack is great!
This is what's games should be about, no micro transactions and pay to win bullshit, just a genuinely hard yet seriously fun game.
The game constantly punishes the player for no reason. Success in this game is more down to pure luck than skill! If I knew this sooner, I would not have purchased this game...

content: Amazing, desperate atmosphere in this game.  Have failed many times so far but enjoy trying again, discovering new encounters, and desperately attempting to find the right balance to survive the trek.  Easy recommendation for this game.
only issues is i hit a point where the best ship i can find cannot reach beyond a bubble, and none of the reachable systems have a longer range ship/technology.  hit this barrier every time
The game is wonderfully entrancing. But I would pay a dollar or two for "save" functionality ("for sissies" add-on :)
Visually great. A satisfying challenge. So replayable.
Best space game after FTL , addictive and fun to play but sometimes a bit to random and impossible to survive
Really challenging and addictive!
Loved it

I have spent hours playing this and was very fun, the random events are really cool, however once i was warped "out there" to a group of 3 stars which i could not get out of and had to restart. also the saving needs to have a little work on it. otherwise 5 stars!
Fun fun
Amazing!
By the replay value of this game
Enjoying it more now that I'm playing a little less conservatively... Still wish it had a bit less of a pure luck element to it.

Many games focus on blasting aliens in space to stay alive. Out There focuses on surviving the harsh environs of space in order to survive. Oxygen, Hydrogen and Iron are more valuable than Gold, and a deficiency in any of them can spell your doom. Retro roguelike gameplay and a psychadelic soundtrack make this game a unique and addicting experience.
Great game.  Wish there were more like this.

What distinguishes Out There from its competitors is the writing. Managing limited resources to survive is fun and all, but the quality of the writing (and the sheer number of random encounters, along with other content) is what really makes this game extraordinary.

Update: hope they will be some updates because the end is not that great,  will be better if they were no end at all.                                              A very good game,  nothing special to say,  we want to replay this game over and over again,  it's hard so it's good!
Really fun story and gameplay. Unique play every time you start a new game.
One of the best mobile games ive played

Great game.  But after beating it twice the game just feels hollow.  There is no substance here and way to much is attributed to luck.  Skill is not needed.  It is hard to say this isn't a good game.  It is just not a grwat game.  Sadly it never gives the player a reward.
This is a beautiful, atmospheric piece of art masquerading as a video game. If you've ever been fascinated by the stars, you owe it to yourself to give this game a shot.
Reminds me of the Faster Than Light, a PC game.
VERY addictive. Super fun. I just wish there was some way to continue after you reach an ending. Like maybe an "endless survival mode" to see how long you can endure.
A really solid game with a strong concept and execution, there are flaws but nothing to warrant anything below 5 stars.

If I didn't have to reinstall the game every time I want to play it I would definitely give it 5 stars. If I get a call or read a text while playing I get the good old 'unfortunatly out there has...' message and it will not reopen unless I install, therefore I will be getting a refund.
Difficult because it requires you to be lucky. Strategically not difficult basic resource management will get you where you need to go.

Great in theory but the ridiculous fuel demands on every action with so little chance of getting more makes it practically unplayable since it is impossible to do anything without running out within two or three jumps.  That's not a clever challenge, just an irritating imbalance that ruins the fun before you can even get into it.
Best rogue like I've ever played.
Great game. As close to FTL on an Android phone as you can get currently.
A game made perfect on this platform. Doesn't get a five because of what I see is a flaw in the gamemechanics. Worth every crown.

This game is as close to old-school Starflight as you will ever find.  It's  brilliantly written, with unique, gorgeous graphics.  The unraveling of the plot is compelling, with a difficulty that will keep hardcore gamers coming back for more, like FTL.  The strategy is unique, concentrating on utilizing scarce resources.  Don't let a few bad luck runs scare you off, half of the thrill of the game is discovering how to best play.
This game is epic.
Love the game but it freezes sometimes and I wish we could take the resources when we change the ship.addictive excellent game
I finished it though it was kinda easy maybe more ships tech and scenarios would be great ad maybe the ability o keep playing after beating it
Everything I ever wanted in games.
Pretty Entertaining
Great game unless you have terrible luck.
It's a very fun survival game with a choose your own adventure feel in it.
Entertaining to play, and has a lot of replay value.  I have yet to see all the different bits of technology or reach the "end".
Awesome game

This game relies too much on dumb luck to overcome its random nature. No matter your skill, you will eventually succumb to events beyond your control (like running out of fuel because there aren't enough gas giants to harvest from). While that's probably how it would be in real life, it makes for a poor game.
Great alternative to FTL, tons of replay value. Great game
Compratelo a occhi chiusi, vi terrà svegli la notte
Nice, engaging eye candy and musak accompanied by a great storyline. Totally worth the pennies.
Great game.  Interesting theme, and challenge.
Awesome rougelike game.  Definitely a space opera with excellent sounds and music. The writing on this is superb. Well done
Amazing and emersive. A rare gem of the space opera genre.
Elite style game. Great game. But very hard to play. We need to save funcionality

Great game I've loved every moment of it's quirky and often unsettling story. It's maybe intentional but when there is no telescope you can still travel far distances east-west but not north-south due to wide-screen phone dimensions. Perfectly stable and such a pleasure to play though.
Even though every journey seems to end it death, probably the most entertaining android game I've ever played.

I didn't expect when purchasing the game that it's designed to be so difficult that you typically only survive a few star journeys. A playthrough pretty much lasts only ten minutes. You usually die from some random event you have no control over. Then you have to start all over again and lose all progress. Some people might enjoy challenges like this, I simply find it frustrating.
Almost no strategy, just randomly hope you get the right materials to survive.

Fantastic. Going to new solar systems is like flipping pages in a space odyssey novel . Simple point and click game play style with beautiful backdrops and lovely music. You move to a solar system, collect supplies from planets like Mass Effect, sometimes also discovering an abandoned ship you can take over. Excellent writing and an enjoyable story arc. Well worth the money.
A well designed game with innovative mechanics. I will be looking forward to any new independent projects this particular game studio creates.

I can't recommend it enough. Wonderful art style, music, and sense of desperate loneliness mixed with optimism. Brutality tough but rewarding as you learn from your mistakes. Even the imperfect English translation adds a certain charm.
This game is exactly what I was looking for. Its a pain to do anything but once you understand what you need to do, its the best time killer I've ever found.
Awesome atmosphere, music, and good reading too. Well executed game!
simplistic but has a real skill to pick up. conservation is key  I've lost count of how many good men and awesome ships I've lost.  it's my mission to complete. stripped down ftl.
Highly recommended!
Grat game. But no save opt
This reminds me of rebuild game, but a thousand miles better, more randomness, more things to do and much harder.

It reminds me of the choose your own adventure stories I read as a kid. I love the randomness of the universe and how dire the survival situation is. The only real gripe I have is that I wish the game could be longer.., like say multiple parts after you reach the end of a story line.  Anyway, it can also be a cold and unforgiving universe, much like my ex girlfriend one wrong move can be your last or at least lead to many hours of suffering, so the faint hearted and easily frustrated need not apply.

I find the fact that you can't move on the system map extremely frustrating. This has been the 7th promising outcome ruined. I could not move around my view, even though my space folder range was huge. Then I will give it four stars. (The People Death are so unfair, previous systems free of their control become infested by their stupid fleets. You should be able survive the initial attack and to get through their blockades if you have a shield + void fluctuator/superconductors, or maybe fire a Laser system)
Poignant, foreboding, occasionally hopeful. I look forward to spending many hours lost out there.

I really hated it... I finished it in like 5 hours and that green ending thing is so disappointing. It's like those films with nonsense end. I really thought it was a joke when I saw 'the end'... Seriously?...
It has nothing really to compare it to but if you like space and exploration than I think you'll love it
Gorgeous art style, witty writing. Equal parts create your own text adventure and part classic space sim "Elite" wrapped up in a retro futurism comic book style. Classic and tough
Best game for the Android I have ever played. Challenging, but very rewarding. Love the alternative endings. Good replayability.
Great fun. So hard. You'll die. Lots.
Impossible to get anywhere in this game and then start back at very beginning
