content: You're more likely to die than win, but the game has a rich atmosphere, lots of space to explore, and good writing, with that same "just-one-more-jump" syndrome you get in games like FTL. Excellent for burning an hour or two, with tons of replayability.

Very captivating. Every game is unique and the more you play it, the better you get at surviving. Even still, because the game changes every time, you never know if the next star system you visit will be your last.
Good resource management game. A bit different but really payable.
One of the few games on Android that keep taking me back
ABSOLUTELY AMAZING AN MUST BUY FOR ALL TYPES

Massive replay value, Nintendo hard, excellent use of simplistic graphics, extremely addictive, brilliantly written. I cannot say enough good things about this game. Got it during a half off sale and I feel like I didn't pay enough. I hope for updates, hell, I'd even pay for DLC. 10 stars if I could.
Best space based story survival game I have ever played.
Well thought out game with great depth. Loved it
Best game out there period.
This game combines a intersting story a amazing concepts and a great story to draw you in.
Awesome
I keep coming back over and over because its really hard and its a good time.
The balance of luck and skill that this game possesses makes it so much fun to play and play and play again. It's very easy to learn and incredibly tough to conquer, but you'll have fun trying!
Couldn't finish all the endings. A good addition would be like an EASY mode after 10 restarts..
Simple but addictive. Lots of replay! Edit: resources got nerfed, lucky if you make it 5 jumps
Nexus 7
This game doesn't suck. Good job.

This game is worth every cent,  countless hours of replayablility! It's brutally hard and frustrating, but the multiple endings, storyline and random events will keep you coming back for more. Would give 7 stars if I could (get it!?!)
Like a pocket version of FTL. Very challenging and fun, if a little repetitive.

I don't mind games that are tough, as long as there is a chance to beat the odds through clever play. But in this one, it seems that way, way too often it is only just blind luck, rather than skill, that you need to avoid running into unwinnable situations, especially in the early game, which is just plain frustrating.
Great game, different, atmospheric and a little reminiscent of the old 'choose your own adventure' games with a dash of FTL thrown in. Just give it a download!

This game takes the best of some classics like Rogue and Elite, and adds a few twists to keep it fresh and new. The music is haunting, to say the least (I would gladly buy the soundtrack). The graphics are great, but there are still some glitches that break my sense of desbelief. This is an unforgiving game, just like Elite, and I like that (I know there's not a happy ending or winning parade at the end, but an horrific and lonely death among the cold space). I would love to be able to play this game offline, keep the social-scoring element as an option (or lose it altogether) and hope for more updates. Keep up the good work.
replyContent: Hi and thanks for your nice review. You can purchase the original soundtrack here : https://play.google.com/store/music/album/Siddhartha_Barnhoorn_Out_There_EP?id=Bjsrndd2dmi6gqwwujoc4wyqi4i

content: It's scratching my itch for an Android FTL port, could use a few tweaks like an always skip travel animation option.  To the folks giving this low ratings because it's too hard: this game is a space rogue-like not every game is meant to be won. Functioning exactly as intended! Keep it up devs!

content: Great visual style, good sound design, fantastic replayability and chock full of meaningful choice. Not for the easily frustrated, though--you will permadeath die over and over and over... There are definitely some language/translation issues with the English text... But I can't decide if this hinders or advances the atmosphere of the game in the long run. Dev is currently addressing a show-stopping interface bug, so that is a positive.
Fantastic
This game is awesome. It's very much an FTL clone, but I say that in the best way possible. It is well worth the money and highly recommended.

I love the text based events every time I travel I await the story told, there's even decisions you have to make that will either cost you resources or gain them, This is an app I'm willing to put money on plain and simple

10/10 space exploration experienced.  Loved it!

There's also some features that bear no mechanical influence and are useless story wise. The biggest problem, however, is that the game pace depends on a plethora of random variables that can ultimately save or kill you. Also, when you think you've reached the 1st objective, the game ends.
So frickin hard

Random events can ruin your game experience.  It looks like these are your biggest challenge and the nature of these makes them impossible  to get your self prepared. 3 games in the row random teleport to out movement range is a bit too much. The is a fine like between challenging and frustrating- for me it's the 2nd one
Great time killer.  Amazing replayibility. Lots of content.  I am hooked

A thousand players died screaming in the silence of space while you read this sentence. A thousand more will die by the time you finish reading this review.   But one person did not die. Play this game and maybe next time that person will be you.

Simply fantastic. Solemn, meditative, and difficult.

This game while extremely unforgiving is impossible to put down. One warning though...it will occasionally fill you with a desire to through your phone against the wall.....in a good way. This is a.must play for all serious gamers.
Terrrrrrrrrrrrrrrible.
Not very fun, rng makes doing well very luck based and ruins the enjoyment for me. Not a lot of interaction either, choose a planet to go to and hope it doesn't kill you, very, very dull.

It's too friggin' random and just kills you out of the blue or destroys your hard earned technology, and that's not even a glitch in the system, but the way the game is designed.  I know many reviews have said this is the whole point of the game, but this is not fun. It's masochistic.

The game is great, good music, interesting encounters etc. The only thing I'd like, to give it five stars, is a save function as it stands now when you quit out you may lose a few turns or your place completely, other then that as I say good game

I've played countless games like this, but for some reason "Out There" surpassed every single game I've ever played. I think about this game constantly and it has just the right amount of difficultly where you just never give up. Don't listen to anyone who says the game is too hard. It's a strategy game. Deal with it.

When I first picked this game up I played for about 2mins and ran out of fuel. Immediately thought to myself "I'd rather play FTL" . But after awhile I started it up again and decided to try it with a different play style. It's a super fun game! Very well done. You might first think that it's not very much like FTL but it's actually meant to be played like FTL in a way. So if you are having trouble, as it is a very difficult game, try a different approach and I guarantee you'll enjoy yourself.

A very simple game without fancy 3D, fast-paced action or even a multiplayer option. Quite the opposite; you are alone and far - very far - from anyone you know. Through narration, the game is successful in making you feel isolated and vulnerable in a universe that has no particular sympathy for you. Whether you have 5 minutes to spare or a couple of hours, Out There will keep you entertained.
Too random and based on luck to really develop a strategy.
Absolutely incredible. Why did I not find this sooner?
Very repetitive and long.  besides the beginning and ending(s), it also lacks a compelling narrative.  It would be a great first attempt though.
Don't expect to win this every time, just enjoy the ride. Excellent graphics and music, and fun gameplay.
One of the best games...OUT THERE.

I love hard games, I've often played Civilization, Total War and Simcity at top difficulty. I guess playing the lottery would have been a much better use of my money... what a waste.

Not being able to give aliens resources when they are clearly in my inventory.  Latest one today:  Launched a probe collected a load of fuel - but it didn't appear in my inventory.  Now stuck on 0 fuel :(   PLEASE FIX THESE BUGS!  There hasn't been an update to the game in some time...  The fact the developers even state "If you experience bugs during alien encounters, restart a new game" should give you warning.  most of the games I have lost so far have been due to a bug.

This game is rad!

I'm not sure if it was because of the ROM I had installed or the version of android that the ROM was running on but I can play the game now that I've moved onto CM's latest ROM. Out There is a narrative rogue like, where crucial decision making and resource management are the keys to success. If you want a game that feels "fair", this one isn't for you: the universe is apathetic to  your plight, and you'll often fail despite your best efforts.  While the game has substantial content, it could earn that final star by having more, or adding some randomness so correct decisions can't be memorized.
So good. Huge replay value.
The game makes me feel so alone in space, really great audio and game environment design, highly recommended. Kinda tough but once u get the gist of it it's guaranteed adventure

Cute art and nice little exploration game... Until a random event leaves your ship stranded without you being able to do anything about it. Even if you play conservatively you can get killed anytime you jump to a new system.  The game gives feeling of exploration and following a storyline but is really quite shallow. That's the essence of the problem. Alien interactions are repetitive and feel largely meaningless and you quickly feel the lack of depth. Too bad, it felt amazing for about 2 hours.

It says in the description: "WARNING : This game is hard," and it's no joke! You have to think carefully because it is very easy to to reach GAME OVER in no time. You can run out of various resources, have a bad random encounter, and even lose technology at any time. This makes any progress you make feel quite rewarding and also (at least for me at this stage) ensures that games tend to be relatively short. The alien encounters take me back to Star Command on DOS PCs, and the alien language puts me in mind of the Ultima Underworld and having to learn lizardman language, though I don't know for sure if the words are constant from game to game yet. Every decision can pretty much be life or death, and it's fun to have that intensity in a small mobile game. I got it on sale and very glad I did. No paying to win with IAPs either!

The reviews about random events screwing you are spot on.  Its a want to be "choose your own adventure" type game but the random events ALWAYS screw you over! And when the space fleet attacks you, they take over ever star system so you cannot even mine for supplies! And to win you need at least 24+ cargo slots! Biggest ship ive seen has only 20!  Starting ship should be a little better, or easier to find a better one! Not worth paying for imo. Sorry.  I hate giving neg. reviews. I know the work involved...
Excellent space roguelike

Honestly, I was hoping for an FTL substitute. For me personally the game misses that mark by a landslide.  It is well made, the graphics are great, I like the overall style and aesthetic.   Unfortunately Out There lacks any kind of actual gameplay. Outside of following a set of implicit rules (I.e. always keep a single piece of Iron or you are doomed) that you have to learn the hard way, the game is almost entirely luck based. You are doing very little except flipping invisible coins and pushing buttons.

I am pretty addicted to this game since buying it a month ago. I finally made it within reach of the red end goal but it is slightly off my screen so I can't click on the star. There don't seem to be other stars to click on to move the map and I can't move it with finger swiping. This is so painful and it seems like a simple thing to fix :(

NO OPTION FOR SAVING THE GAME - this is big minus and for that I'll rate it with 3 stars.  Just a random screw-you-over options just when you've spent 4 good hours and voila.... "YOUR JOURNEY END HERE" Get used to this line - you'll see it a lot :(((((((((
This game is one of the best out there on android. So unique and refreshing. Only downside is the difficulty factor is incredibly high. Random chance events can end your game with no possible escape.

My new few favorite. Can't put it down.

There is a lot to this game, both from the game-play to the choices you can make as a player. Initially I found the game extremely challenging but after getting the hang of it it began making a bit more sense. I soon realized that fuel was more important than anything else.   The choices you make really are meaningful. I haven't gotten to all of the endings, but one of the ones felt very unsatisfying. I'm hoping that after replaying it I will find a better ending.   The visuals were also rather stunning.  On the depth of the gameplay:  The alien language mechanics were intereasting enough. I soon found out that just by looking at he basic structure of the sentences, you could figure out what was being said with just 1 or 2 words.   "A is B A hate C X is love/hate C?"   This isn't the best example but most of the language is in a very basic sentence and just by identifying what words repeat you can guess the structure. I didn't realize symbolic logic would be helpful in a game like this! That aspect alone is enough for me to say this game has a lot of depth, and that's just one game play feature!
Its a good game but the fact that it has no auto save completely ruins it. You have to start the entire game again if you run out of fuel, which is very often. I uninstalled it.

I don't typically purchase games for mobile devices but I decided to take a leap and purchase this game.  Without a doubt it is worth every penny.  It's a game you can sit down and play for a few minutes (either because that's all the time you have or you die within that time) or for an hour.  It's frustrating and entrancing throughout due to the random events, but each discovery makes you want more.  It's a careful balance between resources, technology, and trying to make it further than in previous games.  And all the while, the game is accompanied by a haunting soundtrack that only improves the game.  Buy now.

This game is BS. The random events can really screw you over, ruining an otherwise great game. You'll work hard to get to a decent distance, then some bullsh*t will strand you somewhere and you'll have to give up on hours of work.

This is a very good game with lots of options, greatly executed. It has atmosphere, lots of different and interesting events, ship systems, etc. Unfortunately, beware that it tends to screw you over with too many random elements. The main objective of the game is keeping the three counters - fuel, oxygen and hull - above zero, while upgrading your ship and getting to the target star system. You have very limited space which shrinks with every new system installed. So the game ultimately boils down to luck. I would like it much more if it required more skill and relied less on random elements. Can't wait to get FTL on Android. It's definitely a superior game. Once I played the game a bit more, I had to lower the score. After getting further in, the game becomes overwhelmingly luck-based. It's not even fun for me anymore. Any sense of accomplishment I had on my what I thought was a seriously lucky and successful run was suddenly absolutely obliterated. Once again, no skill involved.
More irritating than fun...
I think it's a great concept.  However,  it's a very difficult game. Managing resources,  losing tech more often than receiving it.. Pretty irritating.
I may have discovered a minor bug - after a while of playing the game, the skip button during the ftl jump animation stopped working. Reinstalling fixed it though.
replyContent: This bug appears if you disable sound FXs. It will be fixed in next update.

Great fun, lots of unexpected turn of events!
Incredibly immersive (great music always helps), challenging, unforgiving with  your mistakes and very well designed. Still has a little bug when encountering other life forms, but that is rare.

It is an interesting and thoughtful game with great replay potential. It is nice if you have to spend some free time (while getting to work for example). Some interface improvements would be nice though: - bigger font (too tiny for a small devices) - it would be nice to have an ability to spent resources (oxygen, fuel, etc) having the probe/drill tab opened.

Self preservation is the key as you are completely reliant on random events to progress. Frustrating (to a degree) but engaging. One glitch though: if you attempt to encounter life twice in a row on the same planet no alien appears and there's no way back requiring a complete restart, fix required.

I do not game much on Android, but this is the one that I keep installed and come back to when I have a little down time.  The design is excellent and the soundtrack is unique.  The storyline offers different variables that lead to different outcomes.  The challenge of deciding what you should carry with you, how you should plan your journey is incredibly fun.

Life in this game is brutal as you would expect. Constantly adjusting your resources, learning about alien tech. It's incredibly melancholic as most of the time you wind up dead. Warning this game is hard with a very steep learning curve.  Worth the time and effort to play. Recommended, but you may need cheering up afterwards.

content: Challenging and addictive

Is this game hard? Yes. Is this game unfair? No. The very nature of the rogue-like game is the challenges it throws at you. And this game does that perfectly. It makes you lose and it makes you angry, but not in an unfair way that you would simply quit. It throws challenges and test whether you can overcome or not. To be fair, it is almost impossible to have the so-called "best ending" even with the strategies. But since the patch, it is much more possible to actually see an ending.  That being said, devs should also think about making the game little more possible to beat with "other" endings. At the current state, it is nearly impossible to see any other endings besides the "green ending," because of certain "blockage" that game suddenly throws at you. devs should definitely think about lessening this challenge.

This is an awesome totally addicting game. It is like Oregon trail in space, only suggestion is when encountering alien ships you can take over if you could syphon the fuel and O2 from your old ship or the new one. Have had no crash problems at all.

The game is way too arbitrary to be fun.  Do you like random events that just stop the game?  Then this game is for you.  No save function? You got it.  Roll the dice because at any moment the game might take all your fuel and strand you.  You have been warned!  What a ripoff

The more I play, the more I wonder what happens at the end. But I can tolerate losing and starting over from zero because the gameplay itself is so engaging.

I want to give this game 5 stars, but parts are critically flawed. First, if you do your last jump with insufficient fuel it does an off screen dice roll to see if you make it. This is fine, but it should have an exception for if you're jumping to a gas giant. If I just got to a new fuel source the game shouldn't end. Second, there are many times where the stars are too spaced out to connect with the space folder, foward or backwards. Fix these and ill give 5 stars

Although I love the setting and style of this game, it is an extremely shallow experience that conceals its weaknesses with random and plentiful restarts. The best thing about the game is the writing: it's varied, interesting, and (other than the occasional typo) well constructed. Most of the special events fit the setting well and produce a sense of mystery and wonder. It's a shame that you'll hardly ever see them in the sea of generic "you lost/gained x amount of fuel/oxygen/hull" events that make up the majority of random events, of which there is very little variation.  Planet exploration is similarly mundane and repetitive. There are only three kinds of planets and there is almost no variation. Rocky planets offer minerals and a random chance to find a technology. All gas giants are the same and offer no variety, but you'll be seeing them constantly because the game uses fuel usage as its primary method for forcing restarts. If you were hoping to focus on exploration and alien contact, don't bother. The majority of your time will go to trying to keep your fuel levels high enough.  Alien interactions are just as shallow. There's no diplomacy or branching dialogue or even differences between language/culture across species. Every alien speaks the same language and follows one of two speech patterns and gives you the same item if you answer two questions correctly. The questions are as repetitive as the rest of the game, but hidden behind the language mechanic.  Save the $4 and buy a classic sci fi book. The gameplay is nearly nonexistent and the writing isn't good enough or frequent enough to make up for the game's many faults.
replyContent: The update should fix this issue

The fuel will be a big problem, so store Helium as much as possible. Do not do upgrade on small ship, you will get a bigger ship eventually. Get my words 😊
Needs patience, but great fun

This game is okay, but come on I discover all this great technology and I never have enough resources to use it, the game would be more enjoyable if you could stack resources into a stack of 100 instead of 20, just seems kind of stupid, please update and please add this feature, cause without that the game is essentially a worthless waste.

content: Definitely something different and interesting, fun to play.   Needs immersive mode on KitKat as the navigation bar is annoying.

Fairly fun, but often frustrating for wrong reasons, even for a Rogue-alike. Reminiscent of FTL but not as good or as complex, although it has a more interesting story.   Some annoying things are the alien languages being unintelligible for most of a game, that an event can cause you to forget basic and essential technologies, and sometimes you can wander into a dead end or be warped into an unescapable part of the map.

content: Really fun game
Beautiful, vast, endlessly replayable and so very, very lonely. Unlike any game app out there and in desperate need for a sequel .
This game just keeps me coming back for more.

There are a few bugs to be ironed out, but the biggest one I found was that stars destroyed and planets terraformed each give the value for the other in the score screen (no major bugs). Even in its current state this game is just amazing and well worth time and money in my opinion. Good job, looking forward to seeing more from Mi-Clos studios.
Addictive roguelike with complex resource  management.
Great game, failure is a part of fun. No retarded in game shop. No ads. Like space? Like games? This game is for you!

Excelent game. Like others I had my jouney ended because I could not reach in any way the closest next star.  Update: Just lowered the score by one star. This game is very good but there are too many events that screw up the entire session, like forgetting basic technology, being teleported to a system too far away from adjacent stars or even orbitting gas giants and taking 40%+ damage whe you NEED fuel. And yes, I managed to get to one of the endings so I'm not doing too bad of a job.
Must play!
Cool ambient sound with a different story every new game. No issues on my S4 - Bravo devs
Very engrossing. Worth the money.
This game is far "out there" Love it very additive great sound track awesome graphics Easy controls. Very challenging.  10 stars
Wow .. This is awesome. . Every time you play it's different
Awesome game very intuitive, must calculate every move in order to have any success in the game.
This is the best game I have played on mobile since triple town. Great job to the developer.
Very enjoyable game. Especially love the rogue-like element. Makes each decision count! If you are on the fence, just take the plunge. The game is awesome
Very addictive. You really need to strategies your resources. Please give more hydrogen, he and oxygen to lengthen survival. Then I will give 5. Keep up the great work!
There's some strategy to this game but it mostly seems like luck.
The game is too hard and gets repetitive quickly.

content: Love the pacing, love the art.
This game has me hooked. The sense of scale of the challenge ahead of you is massive and worth every death and every minute of your time. Couldn't ask for a better game. Well done Devs!

Mentioned in the cooptional podcast, a very fun and rather hard to master game that needs more love from other potential players. Randomly generated, and mostly full of something new each time, it keeps things interesting and makes you consider your options and what risks they may have. And its not too deep not be a pick up and go game.
Awesome, definitely worth it.

Short review: Choose your own space adventure! Plays like FTL without the battles. Same level of awesome.   Long review: They did replace said battles with epic resource management and alien languages. The graphics are very crisp and the art is amazing with its comic style. The music is a game-changer, haunting and urging you to find new things. The story is engrossing and the numerous choices ensure near infinite replayability. A must have game.

Complex, addicting, and challenging game with a beautiful storyline. The English is awkward in some places and the pace could be improved overall, but neither of those seriously detract from how much I enjoy playing. More diversity in the soundtrack would be nice, too, considering how many times I've died and had to start over.

In really enjoying playing this game!  The "maybe just one more jump" gameplay is addicting and the visual and sound design create a great atmosphere.  I hope updates are planned to expand the scenarios even further.
Super engaging

Core mechanics are fun -- haven't managed to get home yet, but still having a great time.  Minor complaint: I find it frustrating not being able to apply resources directly to systems when drilling or mining. Limited cargo space is one of the fundamental parts of the game, but its very annoying to be low on fuel and not be able to dump all of that mined resource directly into your ship without tossing half your other supplies overboard. I would even be okay with it if you could only apply 'on ship' resources to systems, so you throw away one resource and then drag new ones on to the ship, then on to the system and repeat. There's nothing worse than realizing that you could have repaired your hull first but now its too late :P    Initially, this crashed a lot on my Nexus 5, but after restarting my phone that problem seems to have gone away -- so if you experience that, try rebooting.

This was a very interesting game.  Much like FTL but with an emphasis on survival rather than combat, the graphics and system are simple but all designed. The music lends itself to the game's ambience, and the whole thing is a wonderful experience.  That is, until you reach the end, having had a good run of it and picked up a good ship. Then, you accidently finish the game; there are more questions than answers.   The good thing is it spurs you to play again, but the initial shock of the end devalues it.
replyContent: There are 3 endings. Did you find all of them?

content: Lots of atmosphere and challenge in this great space roguelike.
I am completely addicted.
If you like games like FTL, you need to get this game! Great rogueish hook, "hard" SciFi theme, and good production values make it a winner.
Won't play
replyContent: The update should fix this issue

content: I've had about 2 to 3 hours to play this game and I really like it. It took me a few times to get the hang of it, but it's pretty clear there is a lot of depth. My only gripe, especially since I had to restart often, is to restart the game, you have to go through the intro and everything. A quick restart option would be great. Also a save option... I've often gotten really far to just get stuck because of some bad luck. That make me less eager to play the game when I have to stay from the very beginning.
Seriously, drop the four bucks, it's worth every cent
Crashes constantly on Sony Xperia Z, making this unplayable
replyContent: The update should fix this issue

content: One request: implement immersive full screen mode.
I'd suggest adding multiple difficulty levels to appeal to casual and hardcore gamers.

I love this game! Very addicting, fun, and interesting. Would like to see more trade content with aliens at space stations. also, I might be a noob, but it seems I can only go so far with my resources. it makes getting to my goal incredibly hard. Seems too reliant on luck, but that's kinda the fun of it. I also got stuck on a star system and couldn't go anywhere :/ which really sucked cuz it was the furthest I had gone.

I really don't ever write a review, feels too much like paying for a game twice. This game is different, it is simply mind blowing, everything from the comic book style of the game to the classic Scifi feel of the setting. A must play for anyone who loves Space, and even those who aren't particularly fascinated with the subject. A few silly grammatical errors and other such typos prevent me from giving this game the five stars it deserves. When the game fixes those few small flaws, I will re-rate the game to five.
It feels very unfinished, like a proof of concept. I regret my purchase.

I got hit by an event which transported me to a star that I wasn't targeting and from there I did not have the range with which to go to anywhere else thus ending my journey,because of bad game design.Other than that the game is far too reliant on luck,in FTL you needed both luck and skill to pull it off,here there is no skill needed,the game either gives you what you need or it doesn't.

If you liked FTL, this game is for you. Perma death and random encounters can be frustrating but help craft a unique experience each time you play. The simple visuals and text description all help to create an atmosphere of isolation. No adverts, no pay to play = great.

No saves is a good thing I think and I dont mind the situations where you luck out and die having done nothing wrong. The game is well illustrated. A steep learning curve and initial challenge. However didnt take long to get in a position where I could go wherever with no worry about resources. More storage related custimisation would be good and simultaneous handling of resources like mining and repairing for example
I can't stop playing
Very addicting game, kinda reminds me of FTL
Great art, addictive, incredibly fun.
Inventive and brilliantly executed.  Would be nice if it supported immersive mode.

One of the more polished mobile games I've ever played. Lovely art and music coupled with an interesting story. Plays very much like FTL without combat, focusing instead on exploration and resource management. It's quite difficult so don't expect a cakewalk. The pace is excellent allowing the game to be put down and picked up at will. I would recommend it to pretty much anyone.

This is a fantastic game with a hell of a lot more depth than I was expecting. My only issues with this version are the lack of support for immersive mode and the fact that the skip button doesn't work while warping. Those aside, it really is a great game and I highly recommend it.
Enjoyed every minute of this game, great art style, great writing and great repeatability.
This game is super addictive with ALOT of replay value. Definitely one of the best games on Android.

I can't praise this game enough - it is fantastic. A space exploration game with depth and replayability.  It is let down by constant crashes, which after 4 hours play is beginning to become intolerable.  If it geta fixed definitely worth buying,, however anticipate some frustration at the moment.

Stop reading this and get it now. Still here? You're wasting valuable play time. It's a beautiful, fun rouge-like with exploration and resource management. If you like FTL or Star Command. Get. This. Now.
Unique and engaging. I recommend!!!!
Highly recommended, particularly for fans of roguelikes. Because of the fantastic art and music, it would really benefit from using Android's immersive mode to hide the on screen buttons.

This game is a well thought of, and challenging piece of work. It's both beautiful and creative, a good survival game and getting to adventure through space using and collecting resources. Going to planets that contain life and interacting with them.

I like the mechanics and the style is amazing, but it feels like something is missing. Without the frantic combat of FTL, this game relies too much on luck for its difficulty. After a while the playthroughs get repetitive and the game loses some of its lustre. I would tweak the resource requirements to make it slightly less crushing, or add some sense of progression between playthroughs. Overall it's a good effort and just a few tweaks away from being great. Definitely worth playing if you like FTL or other rogue-lites
There's  not much use of other Materials. Fuel and Oxygen is almost the only thing we need but then why are we looting     stacks of Silicon or Au?  Feels undone.
I was in tutorial and my space folder was destroyed jumping to a system with nothing in it, stranded and had to give up... Hope this doesn't happen often...
A well thought out space adventure rogue like, well worth the money
Nice game! Based on the old space exploration game Elite, played in MS Dos a long long time ago. Fun!
Excellent game from what I've seen, but now keeps crashing on my Xperia Z, unfortunately.
Just as hard and addicting flappy birds. Except much much better.

Wasn't sure what to expect, but I enjoyed every aspect of this game from the randomized playthroughs, to getting lucky enough to find all the amazing tech upgrades and ships out there. Fantastic game overall, replayed it many times already and will continue to do so. It would be great if the devs had updated content in the future. New ships, tech, random events, etc. 5 stars as it currently is though!

Great strategy rogue type game, no real battles per say but there are times when you are attacked. One downfall is once you reach the "Quest" the game ends and you can't continue exploring which I hope gets changed

This is a great game! If you like roguelikes, space, survival or choose your own adventure games this is a game you will want to play.  I made the mistake of buying this game late last night and didn't get to bed until 5am. Not gonna knock a star off for that though.
So good to see a high quality mobile game. Its a rougle like with random encounters. Its ftl minus the crw but much more focus on resources. Highly recommend this.
The is no doubt if this game came out before ftl it would be even more popular. It's amazing.

I'm enjoying this game, and is definitely worth the money BUT there are issues. I can easily get stuck with too little resources, no way to get them, and no option but to quit out. I was also shot of to a spiral arm with no way to get out (think Q from Star Trek).  SUGGESTION TO DEV - make a system whereby you can bastardise components or materials at a much higher cost if stick.
The game is awesome, but at times a think the luck element is a bit strong... Quite often, the game will just screw you with random events... There should be alternate ways to generate fuel too...

I understand why some would want to have a save game feature especially when it's quite an expensive game. But it's still acceptable to me. However having history of info of what I have collected in previous games would be useful so I don't go on suicide missions.

Love the visuals, music is great, gameplay is a joy. Few comments, there are quite a bit of typos here and there that need work. And consider having learnt words save across all of your files, adds a sense of progression to the game.

Its a good start, Im looking forward to updates. I get that its a rogue-like etc but its really brutal, to the point of not wanting to continue playing. Resource management is in the toilet, and is frustrating. It was stupid how my game ended when I met the architects, I expected to be able to keep playing as I was finally on a decent roll. The unavoidable random events (like being attacked by enemies for the first time) totally cripple you and destroy your hope of progressing. Needs some spell checking too
Oregon trail in space? Beautiful music? Tons of replayability? Yes Yes and yes. Purchase this game and enjoy one of the best games in the last few months.
Played a couple of games so far but very nice work,  maybe it is possible to create a good mobile game.
Insanely beautiful game
Different each time. The ability to save would be really nice though.
Amazing!
Best game I've played on android.  Very good.
I'm still pining for FTL on Android, but this is a pretty great space-based roguelike that's optimal for touch devices. Absolutely worth the price.
Random and unforgiving. You can do everything right and lose frequently due to random events. Unfair
You have to get in the mood but if you can,  it is a very nice game,  simple but with a lot of replay possibilities.

This game is brutal, emotionally. Like a good roguelike death is permanent, but random factors will often tip the balance.  This leaves you emotionally invested in your progress in moments where the hopelessness of your situation is apparent.  But amazingly, the slow reveal of story elements, and your ability to shift your strategy as you replay, based on an assessment of the risks makes replay nearly mandatory.  You just want to try again.   Not a game for the easily frustrated, but worth it to me.
Kind of reminds me of 'weird worlds: return to infinite space'
It needs different modes for different levels, like language isn't forgotten, pick your ship, or have access to the technology when you learn it for the next play through.
It's amazing, it's like FTL for mobile but minus the fiddly micro management but with more brooding dark atmosphere. Worth every penny. I just missed out on 3 hours sleep playing this.
It's da bomb!

This game is indeed fantastic. Its beautiful, witty, and a great resource mgmt game. Unfortunately, even if you do a perfect job of playing, bad luck will kill you. For example, you are humming right along and ZIP...you are transported into an unplayable situation. Recently, I was playing and I had several cargo squares packed w fuel.  But, I encountered 3-4 star systems in a row that contained aliens...so I couldn't get resources.  I eventually ran out of fuel and died. Annoying as heck!
An amazing space survival game, mechanically perfect, addictive, fun, yet horribly difficult. This is the perfect mobile game, let down only by a few grammatical errors.

This is a really good game, I love the fact that it doesn't have combat in it. Lots to discover. Like others I find it annoying to get stranded by warp events but I guess that's the peril of a randomly generated game map.
Is difficult to find particular resources would be good to add a sort of accumlation so you can upgrade slowly

A truly amazing survival game which perfectly captures the sense of lonliness and exploration in space. Thrilling and worth replaying time and time again. Quite difficult, but my only issue is being forced to quite thanks to being stranded after an event
Excellent exploration. Gives a sense of discovery, and has enjoyable story elements.
Addictive,  frustrating, annoying, brilliant and fun. I don't usually play phone games but this was great.
Great!!! More quests please!
Easy to get to grips with but it gets difficult and more challenging as you progress. Highly addictive.
Out there, searching for meaning, answers, connections, life.
Gamhba ehoilt Xraygoggles Ehoilt Xraygoggles Danour jackta Ehoilt Xraygoggles Danour Karlke Karlke Jacrta Ehoilt Xraygoggles Manels $3.99
Excellent gameplay, the resource management requires some patience but it's really fun. The best survival game I have played on mobile.
This game is a lot of fun if you like exploration games. No combat but lots and lots of random encounters. Star command wishes it was this good.
Fun original survival roguelike
I have heard great things about it but I can't even play it. Please fix.
So addicting!
Best game in quite some time!
I love the game but it crashes constantly, fix that and I'll give it 5 stars!
Ok really liking this game. Looks slick, cool music and an awesome overall concept.... But, keeps crashing on Xperia Z.... I'll wait in hope for a fix :-)

This game is probably the best mobile game I've ever come into contact with. After the Flappy Bird and it's minor clones, I was very distraught with the phone gaming industry. Thank you for restoring my faith and inducing a well-placed addiction, Mi-Clos Studio!
Rock hard but great fun  and very addictive
Poor translations,  very very limited "gameplay".
Excellent

Great space survival "sim." Small choices regarding resources and items can have dramatic consequences when you least expect. Captures the mystery and desperation of deep space travel, with enough humor to keep things engaging. Rocketman!! (Nexus 5)

Very interesting and challenging game. You really need to think and plan your moves die to the scarcity of resources. I've failed tons of times just because i lacked or misused some of my fuel, etc.  Things to improve upon: 1. Can we skip the intro please?  I know there's a button for it but it seems like it takes longer than necessary to play a game. Also, do I really need to pick Play or Tutorial every time I decide to play? 2. The skip button doesn't work when using the Space Folder
Thematically feels similar to FTL, though the game play isn't really the same at all.
What a great game, simple, atmospheric, very relaxing. Grab your spacesuit, sit back and explore 😀
Crashes all the time!
This game speaks to the Star Control player in me.
Only thing missing is immersive mode on 4.4, once that is implemented this game will be perfect.
The style is very attractive and the story is classic. Addictive, but needs more.
I always wanted a game that was like FTL but without the combat, and here it is! I'm really enjoying it.

Gorgeous game, fantastic visuals, sound and narrative. Excellent mix of exploration and tension as you try to push further out into space, manage your supplies and encounter unknown races and advanced technologies. Any rogue-like fans should love this (it doesn't share all aspects of a rogue-like, but the tension created by perma-death is one). Highly recommended for all.
A really great game.
I can't believe how good this is
Very high replayability which is  what I look for in mobile games

Out There is very much as it states, it's out there. If you enjoyed FTL on the PC or Star Commander on Android, you'll love this game. Though this game doesn't have any of the combat (from what I've played) but it does have that sense of urgency and always hanging on by the tips of your fingers suspense. From resource management, to talking to alien races that you can't understand, to making possible game-ending decisions, this game is enjoyable every sing moment. I could brag about this game all day.
Very slick presentation. But really? Tap. Tap. Tap. You're dead. New game. Tap tap tap tap tap tap tap. You're dead. How is this fun? What am I missing? FTL is a much better game.
This is a must Have guys survival space . What more do you need

I don't usually review games, but I felt like this was a game that needed to be brought to people's attention. While it's not a perfect game with a little time and patience it is one of the best survival games I've played. With a focus on resource management rather than combat it's a definite change of pace from most games. If you're a fan of survival games, you need to play this game.

I've already put several hours into this game. The developers have done a great job of portraying a sense of isolation and being in an alien universe. The aliens are truly alien since none speak english. You do learn pieces of their language with each interaction. The touch controls work very well and so far it is running flawlessly on my Nexus 7.

Looks like a really great game of space exploration and an intriguing story is appearing, but because its so hard, it becomes just a falling survivial game. It's also almost completely based on luck, so not much playing satisfaction. You might die really early, without making any wrong decisions or you might die later just by some random chance.  It's got loads of redundant screens.  The fact that you start each time from the beginning also means it doesn't have much long term value.
replyContent: Yes it's a difficult game and it needs strategy. Please head over at the TouchArcade forum for help http://forums.toucharcade.com/showthread.php?t=220379

content: Love the exploration, finding and upgrading tech and the desperation of keeping supplies from running out on your lonely journey.

The learning curve is steep and the game really hard, but I really enjoy playing it and everything in the realisation (music, graphics, texts) is pleasant. I will update when I have played more but now I love it.
...I'm thinking of quitting my job so I can play it more...

This is the kind of game I've been looking for since rymdkapsel. A fathomable sense of loneliness, hauntingly beautiful soundtrack, and great game play.  You need to manage resources, make tough decisions, and have a little bit of luck. People that are complaining a little, games like this shouldn't have saved progress, and they need to be a little tough.  Life is about prioritizing and thinking and making decisions that have consequences, the unpredictability and atmosphere of this game make it absolutely worth. every. penny.
I didn't seem to get very far but I'll play it again for sure.  I though no bakes would be boring but it's great.
I really do want to love it but I can't get past a few areas before it crashes. Currently running an LG G2
An interesting mix of well written space story and resource management. Somewhat similar to FTL, but far less shooty.
It is also fun
Like Faster Than Light, minus the battle, plus resource management and crafting. Highly recommended
Great fun! Solid difficulty which I enjoy immensely
Addictive yet so frustrating, inventory management is a strong must. Think ahead before you do anything!

I'm having fun with this game but at least two things I would like the dev to consider: 1. Like another user I was trapped after an event wrap...2 Can I spend my H, He, O, Fe during mining resources instead of before/after?
I thought it was a little too short  but awesome graphics and concept. Surprise ending

I wish there was a way to save progress... I understand that it goes against the concept of the game.  However, starting over each time you make a bad decision is infuriating... at least give a user an option to select different difficulty levels...
Exploration and upgrades give good depth. Was frustrated that my game was ended when a warp stranded me in a system wasn't close enough to any others.

Ok, the game is amazing with one small exception.  I get really annoyed when I have a completely full inventory, and I can't pick up something I found from an event because it doesn't give me the opportunity to do any inventory management.  Fix that one thing and it moves from really good to amazing (its mostly just a minor annoyance).
Sounds like a great game, however it crashes on my Xperia Z before I can start the tutorial. Hopefully a fix can come soon. I can't wait to play it.
replyContent: We are working on it!

content: Stunning game
Super impressive!
This is a great game to just pick up and play. Completely unforgiving, but so well thought out to bring you back looking for more.
I love space exploration games and this one seems to fit the bill just great.

I have been looking for a rogue-like of this quality on Android for a long time. Every action has a consequence and resource usage must be carefully calculated.  Both the sense of loneliness and the sensation of being the alien in a strange new area of space are brilliantly realized. Well done Mi-Clos.

Interesting but a little difficult. I haven't gotten much reward out of playing so far. Trial and error and replay are very much the order of the day with this title. Excellent atmosphere. Not nearly as much of a micromanage sim as FTL. A step in the right direction for space rogue-likes.
Looks fantastic on my N7
Rogue-a-like meets FTL, with great atmosphere and a real sense of exploration.  Tough game, but very good.

An atmospheric space exploration and survival game with beautiful art direction, a moody soundtrack and slow paced but sometimes tense gameplay based around discovery, resource management and risk taking. You'll fail often, but you will want to keep playing just to see everything that is Out There.
